[normal]2.1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Advanced Enzyme Science Limited (AESL) is a UK based company that has developed an innovative polymer technology based on enzymes (Enzymoplast), which breaks down the C-H bonds in the synthetic polymer chain thereby pr
[normal]o
[normal]ducing CO
[normal]2
[normal] and water in the biodegradation process. The company was founded in England in 2011, although Research and Development has been carried out since 2000. AESL is the Intellectual Property owner and therefore owns all production and distribution rights worldwide. The Head Office is in Ba
[normal]l
[normal]ham, London where all administration, finance and Sales and Marketing fun
[normal]c
[normal]tions are carried out.
[normal]2.2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The UK Market for biodegradable Plastic is significant; AESL is an export-oriented business with a global Distributor network in place. The unique nature of the proprietary technology will allow AESL to grow over the coming years and should place it as the number one technology in the biodegradable, compost
[normal]a
[normal]ble and recyclable plastics market globally. 
[normal]2.3
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Declaration of Interests. AESL networks its products through a global distrib
[normal]u
[normal]tion network. AESL is not a manufacturer of plastic bags and seeks to present facts and information about Enzymoplast technology. 
[normal]3.1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Enzymoplast®
[normal] is an additive which uses specific enzymes with other plant-based components in the form of a Master batch. The Master batch is added and mixed during the further processing of polyethylene into an end product. Under certain environmental conditions the finished product will significantly, biologically-degrade within a few months dependant on the prevailing conditions at End-of-Life. 
[normal]3.2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Enzymes are special proteins which are present almost everywhere. For exa
[normal]m
[normal]ple, certain enzymes decompose food in the stomach or are used for cheese production, cleaning products, washing-up liquid etc. Enzymes act as a 
[normal]“Biocatalysator” and accelerate biochemical processes.
[normal] Enzymes are natural living beings and are therefore especially environmentally friendly.
[normal]3.3
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]An enzyme is only able to decompose one single substrate because of its stru
[normal]c
[normal]tural configuration.
[normal] Therefore there is an extremely wide diversity in enzyme species; each enzyme has an active, as well as a passive, side. The active part of the enzyme fits like a ‘key’ into a lock. The enzyme lodges itself into the a
[normal]p
[normal]propriate portion of the substrate (similar to a round peg in a round hole). 
[normal]As soon as this “Enzymatic Reaction” has started, the substrate begins to be converted back into its basic components. 
[normal]It is important to mention
[normal] 
[normal]that the enzyme
[normal] 
[normal]does not die
[normal] 
[normal]or
[normal] 
[normal]inactivate after this reaction,
[normal] 
[normal]but
[normal] 
[normal]moves on
[normal] 
[normal]to the next
[normal] 
[normal]substrate in the chain reaction to restart the process.
[normal] 
[normal]F
[normal]igure
[normal] 1
[normal] 
[normal]illustrates
[normal] 
[normal]this process:
[normal]Fig.1
[normal].
[normal]This enzymatic reaction process is verified by numerous well-founded studies. Thus, it is undisputed that enzymes actually work – hence it is quite unde
[normal]r
[normal]standable that polyethylene can also be biodegraded by enzymes.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.4
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]As early as 1992, among others Pometto et al. published a scientific study of the possibility of the biodegradation of polyethylene by means of enzymes. Sc
[normal]i
[normal]entists agree that enzymes are present in soil, which can decompose polyethy
[normal]l
[normal]ene. However, so far these enzymes could not be identified and also their exact function is not fully understood. Above all it was never possible, despite years of research, to influence the speed of the decomposition.
[normal] The scientists at AESL have now discovered the mechanics of these enzymatic reactions in polyolefin. 
[normal]3.5
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The solution is not just a single enzyme, but six specific ones out of about 250 thousand different types of enzymes, so-called Multienzymecomplexes, which interact or co-operate with each other to regulate themselves. 
[normal]Reverse engineering in this case is almost impossible. The Multienzymeco
[normal]m
[normal]plex is “encapsulated” into LLDPE, which serves as a carrier for the further processing of polyethylene products.
[normal]3.6
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Polyethylene is difficult to biodegrade mainly due to its high molecular weight and the non-polar C-C and C-H bonds. Furthermore the macromolecular pol
[normal]y
[normal]mer chains have a very dense branch, which results in a low total surface area. Thus, no water or oxygen can normally penetrate into the interior of the basic material. In addition, antioxidants may be added during the manufacturing pro
[normal]c
[normal]ess to prevent an oxygenation reaction.
[normal] 
[normal]3.7
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Once the enzymes are activated in the polyethylene, the biological degradation starts at the weakest link in the polymer chain. Thus, the molecular mass is r
[normal]e
[normal]duced and other microorganisms and fungi can start to decompose the modified polyethylene. The incorporated enzymes promote the growth of the correspon
[normal]d
[normal]ing organisms and cultures, which further accelerate the process until all pol
[normal]y
[normal]ethylene chains are divided into the original substances, Carbon and Hydrogen and then CO
[normal]2
[normal] and water are produced. The aforementioned process is only a
[normal]c
[normal]tivated under certain environmental conditions. This prevents premature biode
[normal]g
[normal]radation, thus allowing the reuse of the product. Listed below are the required criteria similar to any compost or biodegradation process:
[normal]3.8
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Should any one of these parameters be lacking, the process is not initiated and the polyethylene retains its usual properties. The number of microorganisms on the hands, shelf or in a warehouse is not enough to initiate the process.
[normal]3.9
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]A further challenge is how to keep the enzyme alive at high temperatures. E
[normal]n
[normal]zymes normally start to die from a temperature of about 100°C. 
[normal]Therefore the enzymes are especially encapsulated during the production pro
[normal]c
[normal]ess to withstand temperatures in extrusion of up to 300°
[normal]C
[normal]. The precise process of 
[normal]encapsulation 
[normal]forms part of the IP.
[normal]3.10
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The enzymes used do not have a negative influence on the mechanical chara
[normal]c
[normal]teristics of the end products. According to third party tests the characteristics show improvement by as much as 2-3%. However, these values cannot be standardised due to the variety of and types of polyolefin and therefore serves only as a rough guideline.
[normal]Fact 1. Because Enzymoplast is mixed with pure Polyethylene it is possible to recycle ENZO-PE films with other polyethylene products without contaminating the esta
[normal]b
[normal]lished standard polymer recycling stream. Due to the possibility of improvement of the mechanical strength the number of recycling processes may increase. Furthe
[normal]r
[normal]more, Enzymoplast does not use any stabilizers to handle the timeframe of biodegr
[normal]a
[normal]dation. Hence, there is no negative effect as stabilisers weaken polyethylene after a determined time.
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]4.1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The applications are as diverse as the use of polyethylene itself. AESL markets two main master batches, namely ENZO0001 Compostable Grade and ENZO0900 Biodegradable Grade. ENZO0001 usually is for applications where the “End of Life” of the finished product is an Industrial Composting Facility and ENZO0900 for all other applications where no guarantee can be given that the 
[normal]waste collecting system does not fail. 
[normal]The exemption being proposed by go
[normal]v
[normal]ernment is for Biodegradable plastic bags. For the purpose of this evidence, the technology that is being proposed by AESL is ENZO0900. Table 1 shows an example of applications for both ENZO001 and ENZO0900.
